                        <br/><br/><br/><h2>文 献</h2><br><ol><br><li id="R1"><span class='au'>Angulo, P.</span>: <span class="ti">GI epidermiolgy. nonalcoholic fatty liver disease.</span> <span class='so'>Aliment. Pharmacol. Ther., 25, 883-889 (2007)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17402991" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R2"><span class='au'>Day, C. P.</span>: <span class="ti">Non-alcoholic steatohepatitis (NASH): where are we now and where are we going?</span> <span class='so'>Gut, 50, 585-588 (2002)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11950797" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R3"><span class='au'>Patel, K., Muir, A., McHutchison, J. G. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">A link between leptin and steatosis in chronic hepatitis C? Time to weigh up the fats.</span> <span class='so'>Am. J. Gastroenterol., 98, 952-955 (2003)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12809813" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R4"><span class='au'>Chitturi, S. & Farrell, G. C.</span>: <span class="ti">Etiopathogenesis of nonalcoholic steatohepatitis.</span> <span class='so'>Semin. Liver Dis., 21, 27-41 (2001)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11296694" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R5"><span class='au'>Miele, L., Valenza, V., La Torre, G. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Increased intestinal permeability and tight junction alterations in nonalcoholic fatty liver disease.</span> <span class='so'>Hepatology, 49, 1877-1887 (2009)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19291785" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R6"><span class='au'>Lichtman, S. N., Keku, J., Schwab, J. H. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Hepatic injury associated with small bowel bacterial overgrowth in rats is prevented by metronidazole and tetracycline.</span> <span class='so'>Gastroenterology, 100, 513-519 (1991)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1985047" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</spa